---
const chips = [
  { name: "Rose", value: "#E0316B" },
  { name: "Amber", value: "#F5A524" },
  { name: "Green", value: "#42D392" },
  { name: "Cyan", value: "#3CC7F5" },
  { name: "Violet", value: "#9B7CF6" },
  { name: "Coral", value: "#FF7A66" },
];
const sliders = [
  { id: "radius", label: "Corner radius", min: 0, max: 22, value: 10, display: "10px" },
  { id: "density", label: "Density", min: 80, max: 130, value: 100, display: "100%" },
  { id: "fontSize", label: "Font size", min: 85, max: 120, value: 100, display: "100%" },
];
---
<section id="lab" class="chapter chapter--flow lab-chapter">
  <div class="chapter-inner">
    <h2 class="chapter-headline" data-lab-headline>A living system</h2>
    <span class="chapter-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    <p class="chapter-lead">
      A design system is the shared kit a team builds its product from: the colours, type,
      spacing, and components, with the rules that keep them consistent across every screen. I
      lead one at Intrepid called Phoenix.
    </p>
    <p class="lab-explainer">
      Here is a small one, running live. Change a token and every component below updates at once,
      because they all read from the same source. One change, everywhere, with no rebuild. That is
      the work, and it is why teams move faster and stay on brand.
    </p>

    <div class="lab" data-lab>
      <div class="lab-controls">
        <p class="lab-panel-label">Change the tokens</p>

        <div class="lab-control">
          <span class="lab-control-row"><span class="lab-control-name">Accent</span></span>
          <div class="lab-chips" role="group" aria-label="Accent colour">
            {chips.map((c, i) => (
              <button
                type="button"
                class="lab-chip"
                data-chip={c.value}
                style={`--chip:${c.value}`}
                aria-pressed={i === 0 ? "true" : "false"}
                aria-label={c.name}
              ></button>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        {sliders.map((c) => (
          <label class="lab-control">
            <span class="lab-control-row">
              <span class="lab-control-name">{c.label}</span>
              <span class="lab-control-val" data-val={c.id}>{c.display}</span>
            </span>
            <input
              class="lab-range"
              type="range"
              data-control={c.id}
              min={c.min}
              max={c.max}
              value={c.value}
              aria-label={c.label}
            />
          </label>
        ))}

        <button type="button" class="lab-reset" data-lab-reset>Reset tokens</button>
      </div>

      <div class="lab-preview" aria-label="Live component preview">
        <p class="lab-panel-label">Live preview, one real component</p>
        <article class="lab-card">
          <header class="lab-card-head">
            <span class="lab-anno">
              <span class="lab-badge">Popular</span>
              <span class="lab-anno-tag">badge</span>
            </span>
            <span class="lab-price">$12<span class="lab-price-unit"> / mo</span></span>
          </header>
          <h3 class="lab-card-title">Starter plan</h3>
          <p class="lab-card-text">Everything a small team needs to get going.</p>
          <div class="lab-anno">
            <input class="lab-input" type="text" placeholder="Promo code" aria-label="Promo code" />
            <span class="lab-anno-tag">input</span>
          </div>
          <div class="lab-anno">
            <div class="lab-actions">
              <button type="button" class="lab-btn">Choose plan</button>
              <button type="button" class="lab-btn lab-btn--ghost">Compare</button>
            </div>
            <span class="lab-anno-tag">buttons</span>
          </div>
          <div class="lab-anno">
            <ul class="lab-rows">
              <li class="lab-row"><span>Seats</span><span class="lab-pill">5</span></li>
              <li class="lab-row"><span>Storage</span><span>100 GB</span></li>
            </ul>
            <span class="lab-anno-tag">data rows</span>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  // The lab is interactive functionality, so it runs regardless of motion preference.
  import { initLab } from "../../scripts/ds-lab";
  initLab();
</script>
